title: CBT Nuggets - CCNA Data Center DCICT 640-916
description:
Cisco CCNA Data Center 640-916 DCICT by Anthony Sequeira <a href="
https://www.cbtnuggets.com/it-training-videos/course/cisco-data-center-640-916" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
https://www.cbtnuggets.com/it-training-videos/course/cisco-data-center-640-916</a>


This Cisco Data Center training course with trainer Anthony Sequeira covers the technologies of the modern Cisco-centric data center and objectives of the DCICT 1.0 exam. This is the second of two exams required for the CCNA Data Center certification.

Recommended skills:
For the highest degree of success in this course, students should possess the experience and knowledge gained from the CBT Nuggets course Cisco CCNA Data Center 640-911 DCICN

Recommended equipment:
Students are not required to possess any special equipment in order to benefit fully from this course.

01 - The Course Introduction
02 - The Cisco Data Center Architecture
03 - Meet the Nexus Family!
04 - Meet the MDS Family!
05 - Monitoring the Nexus
06 - Exploring vPCs and Their Verification
07 - Exploring FabricPath (TRILL)
08 - You Down with OTV
09 - Virtualizing The Network Device
10 - Virtualizing Storage
11 - Virtualizing Servers
12 - Introducing the Nexus 1000V
13 - Verifying the Nexus 1000V
14 - Storage Options
15 - Fibre Channel and More Fibre Channel
16 - Verifying Fibre Channel
17 - FCoE and DCB
18 - Connecting FCoE
19 - The Nexus 2232 Fabric Extender
20 - The UCS B-Series Family
21 - The UCS C-Series
22 - Connecting B-Series Servers
23 - UCS Management
24 - Pools, Policies, and Profiles
25 - Cisco Load Balancing
